folder: Cannon Street & Delancey Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Cannon Street, at the S.E. corner of Delawcew Street. The view shows both North and South sides of Delancey Street, with the Williamsburg Bridge overhead. The corner building is the Roman Catholic Church of
St. Rose of Lima.
April 4, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.

folder: Cannon Street & Delancey Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Cannon Street, east side, south from Delancey, to and including Grand Streets. Public School No. 110 is shown adjoining the Roman Catholic Church of St. Rosalio, and is on the N.E. corner of Broome
Street.
June 6, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.

folder: Delancey Street & Cannon Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Delancy Street, south side, east from and including Cannon Street, to, but not including Lewis Street. The view shows the Roman Catholic Church of St. Rosalio, at the S.E. corner of Cannon and Delancy

June 6, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

NEG #3337
